              </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">Chairman r</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">ecommends the case is taken to the Privy Council.  </span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">Recommendation:  </span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">I would like the HSC to highlight this case as an example where the GMC ‘</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic">talks the talk’ </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">but </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">stridently and knowingly </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">fails in its core duty to protect patients and public. I would </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">also </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">like the HSC to continue to monitor the progress of this important case.  </span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic">December 2013</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p></div></body></html>